cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.PL

The paper deals with temporal logics and automata, which are typically studied in the areas of logic (cs.LO) and formal languages (cs.FL). The use of Turtle Programs and Rankers suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.AI). Finally, the discussion of interval constraint modalities and their complexity places the paper in the area of programming languages (cs.PL).
